Package org.eclipse.gef.zest.fx.behaviors

package org.eclipse.gef.zest.fx.behaviors
This package provides behaviors for transferring information between graph model elements and layout abstractions ( GraphLayoutBehavior, AbstractLayoutBehavior, NodeLayoutBehavior, EdgeLayoutBehavior), as well as hiding/unhiding of nodes and related edges ( AbstractHidingBehavior, NodeHidingBehavior, EdgeHidingBehavior, EdgeLabelHidingBehavior).
  • Related Packages
    Package
    Description
    org.eclipse.gef.zest.fx
    This package provides a Guice Module ( ZestFxModule) with bindings for Zest.FX, as well a class (ZestProperties) that defines all supported graph attributes for visualization and layout.
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AbstractHidingBehavior
    The AbstractHidingBehavior registers listeners on the HidingModel upon activation.
    AbstractLayoutBehavior
    The AbstractLayoutBehavior is an abstract behavior that schedules AbstractLayoutBehavior.preLayout() and AbstractLayoutBehavior.postLayout() to be called before or after a layout pass, respectively.
    EdgeHidingBehavior
    The EdgeHidingBehavior is an EdgePart-specific AbstractHidingBehavior implementation.
    EdgeLabelHidingBehavior
    The EdgeLabelHidingBehavior is an EdgeLabelPart-specific AbstractHidingBehavior implementation.
    EdgeLayoutBehavior
    The EdgeLayoutBehavior is an EdgePart-specific AbstractLayoutBehavior implementation.
    GraphLayoutBehavior
    The GraphLayoutBehavior is responsible for initiating layout passes.
    NodeHidingBehavior
    The NodeHidingBehavior is specific to NodePart.
    NodeLayoutBehavior
    The NodeLayoutBehavior is a NodePart-specific AbstractLayoutBehavior implementation.
